High-Impact Features

1. Study Session Timer / Pomodoro Tracker

Built-in timer for focused study sessions (25/5 min intervals)
Track total study time per notebook/subject
Break reminders and session history

2. Task/Assignment Manager

Deadline tracking with visual indicators (overdue, upcoming)
Priority levels and status (todo, in-progress, done)
Link tasks to specific notebooks
Calendar/timeline view of all deadlines

3. Search Functionality

Global search across all notes and notebooks
Filter by date, notebook, or tags
Quick find within current note

4. Tags & Organization

Tag notes with keywords (#midterm, #important, #review)
Filter and group notes by tags
Tag-based quick access

5. Note Linking / Cross-References

Link related notes together
"See also" suggestions
Backlinks to show which notes reference current note

6. Export Options

Export notes as PDF, Markdown, or plain text
Batch export entire notebook
Print-friendly formatting

7. Quick Stats Dashboard

Notes created this week/month
Most active notebooks
Study time analytics
Task completion rate

8. Flashcard Generator

Create flashcards from notes (Q&A format)
Study mode with spaced repetition hints
Track which cards need more review

9. Backup & Sync

Auto-backup to local folder/cloud
Export/import entire data file
Version history for notes

10. Dark Mode / More Themes

Eye-friendly dark theme
Student-requested color schemes
High contrast accessibility mode


Quick Wins (Easy to Implement)

11. Recent Notes Panel

Show 5 most recently edited notes on Home
Quick access without navigating notebooks

12. Note Preview on Hover

Tooltip preview of note content when hovering over titles
Helps find the right note faster

13. Keyboard Shortcuts

Ctrl+N: New note
Ctrl+S: Save note
Ctrl+F: Search
Ctrl+T: Insert template

14. Word/Character Count

Live count in note editor
Target word count for assignments

15. Auto-Save Indicator

Visual feedback when note is saved
Prevent accidental data loss